p: Results show that 40 constituents representing 98.93% of the total content were identified in the leaf EO, 11 of them being above 1%. The main constituents in the leaf EO (above 3%) were 1,8-cineole (41.0%), α-terpinyl acetate (14.4%), α-pinene (2.6%), β-elemene (0.78%), sabinene (8.8%), β-linalool (4.9%), α-terpineol (3.1%), α -pinene (2.6%), and terpinene-4-ol (2.4%).
